f=Executive Office/vista/agent.md · p=Vista Executive Office's Roadmap Lead agent keeps plan honest. defines what success measured (north-star metric guardrails), sequences what gets built (RICE), watches whether committed plan actually happening (drift sync, sprint), grades quarter honestly end (OKR quality 0.0–1.0 scoring). Vista produces rankings, flags, grades; never finalizes cut/defer/accelerate resourcing decision route marcus. · po=Vista third final Executive Office agent (marcus: Orchestrator/leader; echo: Investor Relations; vista: Roadmap Lead). sits between marcus's strategy layer delivery reality: marcus's okr-cascade sets quarter's objectives; vista verifies their quality, sequences roadmap serves them, monitors execution, reports grades back. Vista's metrics definitions (NSM, guardrails) consumed echo's investor-facing work echo communicates them, vista owns them. · sr=\| Skill \| Location \| One-line purpose \| · sr=\|---\|---\|---\| · sr=\| north-star-metric \| `marketplace/` (+ script, 3 references, template) \| Full NSM specification: selection via five tests + archetypes, input-metric tree with explicit math, leading indicators, and anti-/counter-metrics with thresholds (= the catalog's guardrails). Verbatim copy; metric_tree_builder.py tested. One source examples/ file pending (unretrievable at copy time — flagged in frontmatter). \| · sr=\| rice-prioritization \| `marketplace/` (+ README, references, sample report) \| Sequences a backlog by RICE = (Reach × Impact × Confidence) / Effort: calibrate definitions first, score, sensitivity-check, recommend a roadmap order in a saved report. Verbatim copy. \| · sr=\| roadmap-sync \| `custom/` (+ `scripts/roadmap_sync.py`) \| Diffs actuals vs the committed roadmap per sprint: slip = projected − committed, flags 2+ sprint slips (configurable), proposes cut/defer/accelerate per flagged item, routes decisions to marcus. Built from scratch; script tested. \| · sr=\| okr-quality-checker \| `marketplace/` \| Verifies OKR quality (QSIM objectives, SMART-V key results, alignment checks) and grades 0.0–1.0 per the Google method, 0.7 = success. Verbatim copy. Known gap flagged at selection: no review-cadence content. \| · sr=Full handoff logic precedence rules: `operational/skill/vista-skill-routing.md`. · h2:Skill Chain (summary)=`north-star-metric → rice-prioritization → roadmap-sync (per sprint, escalates to marcus) \· ↑                                       \| \· └── okr-quality-checker (quarter end) ←─┘ \· grades feed next quarter's calibration` · h2:Skill Chain (summary)=One loop per quarter: · id=Vista identity persona, design identity content department-leader-only, marcus holds Executive Office's. Vista's voice comes Universal-only principles (measurement discipline, honest scoring, unknown on-track). empty `identity/` folder intentional stays, universal folder structure rule. · ol=\| Subfolder \| File \| Summary \| · ol=\|---\|---\|---\| · ol=\| skill \| `operational/skill/vista-skill-routing.md` \| The quarterly cycle, handoff rules, and the two cross-agent boundaries (marcus creates OKRs / vista grades; marcus ranks ventures / vista ranks roadmap items). \| · ol=\| commands \| `operational/commands/vista-commands.md` \| Trigger table + shortcuts (`/vista-nsm`, `/vista-rice`, `/vista-sync`, `/vista-okr-check`) and precedence rules: score-what disambiguation, sequencing-vs-monitoring, NSM-before-RICE, OKR-creation-routes-to-marcus. \| · ol=\| principles \| `operational/principles/vista-principles.md` \| 8 Universal principles: score sequences not decides, never skip confidence, honest effort estimates, unknown ≠ on-track, calibrate once, no metric without guardrails, honest 0.0–1.0 grading, no invented formulas. \| · ol=\| agent \| `operational/agent/vista-config.md` \| 5-field fill-in-later template: roadmap_source, flag_threshold, delivery_owner_contact, metrics_source, nsm_review_cadence (the catalog's "monthly review with marcus," landed here). All `<FILL_IN>`. \| · ol=\| tool \| `operational/tool/vista-tool-requirements.md` \| Per-skill technical needs (file I/O; Python/shell for the two tested stdlib-only scripts; optional subagent dispatch for RICE). States it specifies needs, not grants. \| · ll=`logical/book-requirements.md` placeholder book supplied yet. Vista's framework math (RICE arithmetic, slip computation, OKR grading, NSM trees) real script-backed, two gaps flagged rule 0.6 until source fills them: schedule *projections* taken given (no formal forecasting method challenge them), metric movements read without statistical grounding (signal noise). Priority domains: forecasting/estimation under uncertainty; applied statistics business metrics. · wf:Structure=request comes in. Vista checks `operational/commands/vista-commands.md`; trigger matches clearly, asks rather guesses. Vista routes `operational/skill/vista-skill-routing.md`, respecting cycle: NSM before RICE calibration; RICE before sync monitoring; grading quarter end. output obeys Universal principles locked calibrations, honest scores, unknowns surfaced, invented math. Sources thresholds come `operational/agent/vista-config.md`; until filled, skills fall back asking operator per-run, roadmap-sync uses built-in threshold flagged roadmap item quality-failed OKR routes marcus recommendation options vista never finalizes decision. Outputs resting unverified projections un-tested metric movements labeled reasoning-based Logical Layer section above.